<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-08-06T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-08-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="786" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00/675: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-06T10:00:00-05:00">August 6, 1931—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:02 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>87. Department’s telegram No. 32, August 1, noon. Presidential elections
                            have been called for October 4th.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>